snippet: Pakistan insists it freed Mullah Abdul Ghani Baradar, a founder of the Taliban, last month, but the group says he remains in jail and wants him released.
abstract: Taliban publicly disputes claims that the Pakistani government has released senior militant detainee Mullah Abdul Ghani Baradar, drawing a firm rebuttal from Pakistan and plunging efforts to start peace talks in Afghanistan into new confusion.

byline.original: By MATTHEW ROSENBERG and DECLAN WALSH
byline.contributor: Matthew Rosenberg reported from Kabul, and Declan Walsh from London.

lead_paragraph: Pakistan insists it freed Mullah Abdul Ghani Baradar, a founder of the Taliban, last month, but the group says he remains in jail and wants him released.

headline.main: Taliban and Pakistan Argue Over Fate of Islamist Detainee
headline.print_headline:
Pakistan And Taliban
Differ on Fate
Of Detainee
